                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14519.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-07T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1915—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>395. Department’s 508, March 6, 9 p.m. The note was delivered to General Obregon
                    at 1 p.m. and he has just answered that, “As all matters of international
                    character are not within his jurisdiction he has transcribed the same to
                    Carranza.”</p>
                <p>Please let us know Carranza’s answer as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
